.TH "radeon_fence_wait_timeout" 9 "radeon_fence_wait_timeout" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
radeon_fence_wait_timeout \- wait for a fence to signal with timeout
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "long" radeon_fence_wait_timeout
.BI "(struct radeon_fence *fence "  ","
.BI "bool intr "  ","
.BI "long timeout "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "fence" 12
radeon fence object
.IP "intr" 12
use interruptible sleep
.IP "timeout" 12
maximum time to wait, or MAX_SCHEDULE_TIMEOUT for infinite wait
Returns remaining time if the sequence number has passed, 0 when
the wait timeout, or an error for all other cases.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Wait for the requested fence to signal (all asics).
\fIintr\fP selects whether to use interruptable (true) or non-interruptable
(false) sleep when waiting for the fence.
